shePtpMIB.name: shePtpMIB

revisions.description: Update descriptions and remove not needed parameters from port-table. Add new alarm trap if IpHostInterface config is missing or invalid.
Update parameter syntax and descriptions after review. Add alarmSeverity configuration to portDs.
Correct descriptions for shePtpForeignMasterDSNumberForeignRecords and shePtpForeignMasterDSAnnounceMessages.

shePtpMIB.contactinfo: Gerd Barchmann COO BCS BBA RD SDE HW1 gerd.barchmann@nsn.com +49 3834 555654 sylwester.nawrocki@tieto.com
shePtpMIB.description: This MIB based on ptp-Mib proposal from IEEE1588 workin group. Management Information Base module for PTP configuration, default dataset, current dataset, parent dataset, global time proporties dataset, foreign dataset and port configuration dataset components. New supported with R3.7M.

ShePtpEnableType.name: ShePtpEnableType
ShePtpEnableType.description: Used for show adminState of PTP subsystem in NE.

ShePtpAcceptableMasterSyncStateType.name: ShePtpAcceptableMasterSyncStateType
ShePtpAcceptableMasterSyncStateType.description: used to show the status of configured acceptable master clocks.

ShePtpPortDSIntervalType.name: ShePtpPortDSIntervalType
ShePtpPortDSIntervalType.description: Used to configure SyncInterval and ReqInterval in portDS.

shePtpAdminState.name: shePtpAdminState
shePtpAdminState.description: Enable or disable the Precision Time Protocol on this node. The default value is disabled. Note: SHE system will enable/disable the PTP subsystem via a configuration command in sheSyncMib. This will force an switchover between the system default sync module, which could use T3 or BITS or syncEthernet as sync sources configured and controled via sheSyncMib, and the PTP sync module configured and controled via this shePtpMib module. A modification will only be supported if CXU_B3 is used! All other CXU versions are not able to support timing over packet feature!

shePtpManufacturerIdentity.name: shePtpManufacturerIdentity
shePtpManufacturerIdentity.description: The value of manufacturerIdentity shall be an OUI owned by the manufacturer of the node.

shePtpRevisionData.name: shePtpRevisionData
shePtpRevisionData.description: Indication of the revisions for node hardware (HW), firmware (FW), and software (SW). This information shall be semicolon (;) separated (HW;FW;SW).

shePtpClockType.name: shePtpClockType
shePtpClockType.description: ClockType as defined in the CLOCK_DESCRIPTION management message. Indication of the PTP node type. A TRUE value of a bit in the clockType field indicates that the description applies to the node. 0 - ordinary clock 1 - boundary clock 2 - peer-to-peer transparent clock 3 - end-to-end transparent clock 4 - management node 5..0xF - Reserved

shePtpVersion.name: shePtpVersion
shePtpVersion.description: Version number of supported IEEE1588 release.

shePtpDefaultDSInitializable.name: shePtpDefaultDSInitializable
shePtpDefaultDSInitializable.description: The clock can be reinitialized by a management message.

shePtpDefaultDSTwoStepFlag.name: shePtpDefaultDSTwoStepFlag
shePtpDefaultDSTwoStepFlag.description: Use Follow Up messages or not. Using Follow Up will increase PTP packet rate (2x Sync rate) and CPU load!

shePtpDefaultDSIdentity.name: shePtpDefaultDSIdentity
shePtpDefaultDSIdentity.description: The clockIdentity is an 8 octet (byte) array. The value range of each octet is 0..0xFF.

shePtpDefaultDSNumberPorts.name: shePtpDefaultDSNumberPorts
shePtpDefaultDSNumberPorts.description: Number of available PTP port's in the system.

shePtpDefaultDSClass.name: shePtpDefaultDSClass
shePtpDefaultDSClass.description: clockClass attribute of this ordinary slave-only clock. Default value is 255.

shePtpDefaultDSAccuracy.name: shePtpDefaultDSAccuracy
shePtpDefaultDSAccuracy.description: Part of default dataset clockQuality struct. Characterizes a clock for the purpose of the best master clock (BMC) algorithm. This is an enum value as defined in clause 7.6.2.5, table 6 of IEEE1588-2008 standard. clockAccuracy is related to the time source and holdover specifications of this clock

shePtpDefaultDSVariance.name: shePtpDefaultDSVariance
shePtpDefaultDSVariance.description: offsetScaledLogVariance defaultDS member, it is an attribute defining the stability of a clock. This is the precision of the timestamps included in messages issued by the clock when it is not synchronized to another clock using the protocol. The representation is described in clause 7.6.3.3 of IEEE1588-2008 standard.

shePtpDefaultDSPriority1.name: shePtpDefaultDSPriority1
shePtpDefaultDSPriority1.description: priority1 attribute of this PTP clock. This attribute is used in the execution of the best master clock algorithm, if BMC is used. However in this PTP slave clock implementation SLAVE_ONLY mode is used and priority1 is meaningless in respect of BMC.

shePtpDefaultDSPriority2.name: shePtpDefaultDSPriority2
shePtpDefaultDSPriority2.description: priority2 attribute of this PTP clock. This attribute is used in the execution of the best master clock algorithm, if BMC is used. However in this PTP slave clock implementation SLAVE_ONLY mode is used and priority2 is meaningless in respect of BMC.

shePtpDefaultDSDomainNumber.name: shePtpDefaultDSDomainNumber
shePtpDefaultDSDomainNumber.description: A domain number specifying the scope of PTP message communication, state, operations, data sets and timescale. 0 - default 1 - alternate domain 1 2 - alternate domain 2 3 - alternate domain 3 4..127 - user-defined 128..255 - reserved

shePtpDefaultDSSlaveOnly.name: shePtpDefaultDSSlaveOnly
shePtpDefaultDSSlaveOnly.description: Set to TRUE during initialization and not allowed to be changed as this is a slave-only clock.

shePtpDefaultDSControlRequest.name: shePtpDefaultDSControlRequest
shePtpDefaultDSControlRequest.description: setPtpDefaultDataSet (10): shePtpDefaultDSControlInitializable shePtpDefaultDSControlTwoStepFlag shePtpDefaultDSControlIdentity shePtpDefaultDSControlPriority1 shePtpDefaultDSControlPriority2 shePtpDefaultDSControlDomainNumber

shePtpDefaultDSControlStatus.name: shePtpDefaultDSControlStatus
shePtpDefaultDSControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

shePtpDefaultDSControlTimer.name: shePtpDefaultDSControlTimer
shePtpDefaultDSControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shePtpDefaultDSControlReqResult.name: shePtpDefaultDSControlReqResult
shePtpDefaultDSControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

shePtpDefaultDSControlTimeStamp.name: shePtpDefaultDSControlTimeStamp
shePtpDefaultDSControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shePtpDefaultDSControlDomainNumber.name: shePtpDefaultDSControlDomainNumber
shePtpDefaultDSControlDomainNumber.description: look at group. Range 128...255 is reserved.

shePtpCurrentDataSetStepsRemoved.name: shePtpCurrentDataSetStepsRemoved
shePtpCurrentDataSetStepsRemoved.description: The number of communication paths traversed between the local clock and the grandmaster clock.

shePtpCurrentDataSetOffsettFromMasterSec.name: shePtpCurrentDataSetOffsettFromMasterSeconds
shePtpCurrentDataSetOffsettFromMasterSec.description: Implementation-specific current value of the time difference between a master and a slave as computed by the slave in seconds.

shePtpCurrentDataSetOffsettFromMasterNan.name: shePtpCurrentDataSetOffsettFromMasterNanoSeconds
shePtpCurrentDataSetOffsettFromMasterNan.description: Implementation-specific current value of the time difference between a master and a slave as computed by the slave in nano-seconds.

shePtpCurrentDataSetMeanPathDelaySeconds.name: shePtpCurrentDataSetMeanPathDelaySeconds
shePtpCurrentDataSetMeanPathDelaySeconds.description: Implementation-specific current value of the mean propagation time between a master and slave clock as computed by the slave in seconds.

shePtpCurrentDataSetMeanPathDelayNanoSec.name: shePtpCurrentDataSetMeanPathDelayNanoSeconds
shePtpCurrentDataSetMeanPathDelayNanoSec.description: Implementation-specific current value of the mean propagation time between a master and slave clock as computed by the slave in nano-seconds.

shePtpParentClockIdentity.name: shePtpParentClockIdentity
shePtpParentClockIdentity.description: Identifies parent clock this slave clock is synchronized to. The clockIdentity is an 8 octet (byte) array. The value range of each octet is 0..0xFF.

shePtpParentClockPortNumber.name: shePtpParentClockPortNumber
shePtpParentClockPortNumber.description: Port number of master clock to which this clock synchronizes.

shePtpParentGrandmasterIdentity.name: shePtpParentGrandmasterIdentity
shePtpParentGrandmasterIdentity.description: ClockIdentity attribute of the grandmaster clock.

shePtpParentGrandmasterClockClass.name: shePtpParentGrandmasterClockClass
shePtpParentGrandmasterClockClass.description: Part of grandmaster clock quality struct.

shePtpParentGrandmasterClockAccuracy.name: shePtpParentGrandmasterClockAccuracy
shePtpParentGrandmasterClockAccuracy.description: Part of grandmaster clock quality struct.

shePtpParentGrandmasterClockVariance.name: shePtpParentGrandmasterClockVariance
shePtpParentGrandmasterClockVariance.description: Part of grandmaster clock quality struct.

shePtpParentGrandmasterPriority1.name: shePtpParentGrandmasterPriority1
shePtpParentGrandmasterPriority1.description: Priority1 attribute of the grandmaster clock.

shePtpParentGrandmasterPriority2.name: shePtpParentGrandmasterPriority2
shePtpParentGrandmasterPriority2.description: Priority2 attribute of the grandmaster clock.

shePtpPortDataSetTable.name: shePtpPortDataSetTable
shePtpPortDataSetTable.description: The table containing Port Data Set entries for each port of this clock. For the single port of this clock, ShePtpPortDataSetEntry is maintained as the basis for protocol decisions and providing values for message fields. The number of the table entries is the value of shePtpDefaultDSNumberPorts.

shePtpPortDataSetEntry.name: shePtpPortDataSetEntry
shePtpPortDataSetEntry.description: PTP configuration information for a particular port.

shePtpPortDSPortNumber.name: shePtpPortDSPortNumber
shePtpPortDSPortNumber.description: The value of the portNumber for a port on a PTP node supporting a single PTP port shall be 1. The values of the port numbers for the N ports on a PTP node supporting N PTP ports shall be 1, 2, ..N, respectively

shePtpPortDSClockIdentity.name: shePtpPortDSClockIdentity
shePtpPortDSClockIdentity.description: PortIdentity attribute of the local port.

shePtpPortDSDelayMechanism.name: shePtpPortDSDelayMechanism
shePtpPortDSDelayMechanism.description: Indication of the propagation delay measuring option used by the port in computing shePtpCurrentDataSetMeanPathDelay*. Possible values: E2E (0x01) - The port is configured to use the delay request-response mechanism; P2P (0x02) - The port is configured to use the peer delay mechanism; DISABLED (0xFE) - The port does not implement the delay mechanism.

shePtpPortDSAcceptableMasterEnabled.name: shePtpPortDSAcceptableMasterEnabled
shePtpPortDSAcceptableMasterEnabled.description: Enable/Disable the usage of acceptableMasterTable. The Acceptable Master Table is always used and this attribute value is always TRUE.

shePtpPortDSUnicastNegotiationEnabled.name: shePtpPortDSUnicastNegotiationEnabled
shePtpPortDSUnicastNegotiationEnabled.description: This atrribute determines if the message negotiation is used (TRUE) or not (FALSE) in case unicast communications is used, for any master clock entered in the acceptableMasterTable. This is a global flag to enable/disable unicast negotiation. This flag must be set to true and an entry added to the acceptableMasterTable and the discoveryMasterTable for autonegotiation to be started with given master clock.

shePtpPortDSUnicastNegotiationDuration.name: shePtpPortDSUnicastNegotiationDuration
shePtpPortDSUnicastNegotiationDuration.description: The duration in seconds for which to request unicast contracts. Only relevant for negotiated unicast streams, i.e. to the master clocks which port addresses are present in the shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTable.

shePtpPortDSUnicastLogQueryInterval.name: shePtpPortDSUnicastLogQueryInterval
shePtpPortDSUnicastLogQueryInterval.description: The log to the base 2 value of the request rate (per second) when trying to establish a unicast contract with a remote master device (when it does not respond immediately).

shePtpPortDSVlanId.name: shePtpPortDSVlanId
shePtpPortDSVlanId.description: ID of VLAN used for PTP traffic. This configuration is only a reference to used VLAN - no explicite Vlan create configuration in the NE will be forced by this setting. The interface configuration including IpAddress, SubnetMask and Vlan has to be made via general sheSystemIpHostTable configuration.

shePtpPortDSLogMeanSyncInterval.name: shePtpPortDSLogMeanSyncInterval
shePtpPortDSLogMeanSyncInterval.description: The interval to use for multicast sync messages on this port. This is log2(1/Sync packet rate) PTP version 2.

shePtpPortDSLogMinMeanDelayReqInterval.name: shePtpPortDSLogMinMeanDelayReqInterval
shePtpPortDSLogMinMeanDelayReqInterval.description: In PTP v2 for a slave device this is the preferred interval to be used for transmitting delay request messages but is subject to any minimum specified by the master. Logarithm to the base 2 of the minDelayReqInterval.

shePtpPortDSLogMeanAnnounceInterval.name: shePtpPortDSLogMeanAnnounceInterval
shePtpPortDSLogMeanAnnounceInterval.description: The interval to use for multicast announce messages on this port. This is log to the base 2 of the Announce message rate (per second).

shePtpPortDSAnnounceReceiptTimeout.name: shePtpPortDSAnnounceReceiptTimeout
shePtpPortDSAnnounceReceiptTimeout.description: The timeout period, in announce message intervals, within which at least one announce message must be received.

shePtpPortDSLogMinPdelayReqInterval.name: shePtpPortDSLogMinPdelayReqInterval
shePtpPortDSLogMinPdelayReqInterval.description: The minimum permitted mean time interval between successive Pdelay_Req messages. By default this attribute is initialized to the value of shePtpPortDSLogMeanSyncInterval. This is log to the base 2 of the Pdelay_req message rate (per second).

shePtpPortDSAlarmSeverityIndex.name: shePtpPortDSAlarmSeverityIndex
shePtpPortDSAlarmSeverityIndex.description: This index selects an item in the sheAlarmSeverityProfileTable. It is used to assign the reported alarm to a severity.

shePtpPortDataSetControlStatus.name: shePtpPortDataSetControlStatus
shePtpPortDataSetControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

shePtpPortDataSetControlTimer.name: shePtpPortDataSetControlTimer
shePtpPortDataSetControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shePtpPortDataSetControlControlReqResult.name: shePtpPortDataSetControlControlReqResult
shePtpPortDataSetControlControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

shePtpPortDataSetControlTimeStamp.name: shePtpPortDataSetControlTimeStamp
shePtpPortDataSetControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shePtpPortDataSetControlIndex.name: shePtpPortDataSetControlIndex
shePtpPortDataSetControlIndex.description: The index of port DS for configuration.

shePtpForeignMasterDataSetTable.name: shePtpForeignMasterDataSetTable
shePtpForeignMasterDataSetTable.description: This table is maintained for the purpose of qualifying Announce messages, it is used by best master clock algorithm. There will be an entry dynamically created in the table for each master clock from which Announce messages are received on corresponding (shePtpPortDSPortNumber) clock port.

shePtpForeignMasterDataSetEntry.name: shePtpForeignMasterDataSetEntry
shePtpForeignMasterDataSetEntry.description: PTP configuration information for a particular port.

shePtpForeignMasterDSIndex.name: shePtpForeignMasterDSIndex
shePtpForeignMasterDSIndex.description: Second Index for table, Count of foreign master entries on a port. Foreign Master Data set shall have a minimum capacity of 5 foreign master records

shePtpForeignMasterDSNumberForeignRecord.name: shePtpForeignMasterDSNumberForeignRecords
shePtpForeignMasterDSNumberForeignRecord.description: Count of foreign clock records on a port. This equals to the actual number of foreign clocks from which Announce messages are received. Table shall have a minimum capacity of 5 foreign master records.

shePtpForeignMasterDSClockIdentity.name: shePtpForeignMasterDSClockIdentity
shePtpForeignMasterDSClockIdentity.description: Part of the sourcePortIdentity field value of an Announce message received from the foreign master.

shePtpForeignMasterDSPortNumber.name: shePtpForeignMasterDSPortNumber
shePtpForeignMasterDSPortNumber.description: Part of the sourcePortIdentity field value of an Announce message received from the foreign master.

shePtpForeignMasterDSAnnounceMessages.name: shePtpForeignMasterDSAnnounceMessages
shePtpForeignMasterDSAnnounceMessages.description: The number of Announce messages from the foreign master indicated by the shePtpForeignMasterDSClockIdentity and shePtpForeignMasterDSPortNumber (foreignMasterPortIdentity) that have been received within a time window of duration 4 * shePtpPortDSLogMeanAnnounceInterval.

shePtpForeignMasterDSNetworkProtocol.name: shePtpForeignMasterDSNetworkProtocol
shePtpForeignMasterDSNetworkProtocol.description: Supported PTP transport protocol is only IP/UDP.

shePtpForeignMasterDSProtocolAddressLeng.name: shePtpForeignMasterDSProtocolAddressLength
shePtpForeignMasterDSProtocolAddressLeng.description: Supported PTP transport protocol is only IP/UDP so address length is always 4.

shePtpForeignMasterDSProtocolAddress.name: shePtpForeignMasterDSProtocolAddress
shePtpForeignMasterDSProtocolAddress.description: The IP address of the detected foreign master.

shePtpAcceptableMasterEntry.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterEntry
shePtpAcceptableMasterEntry.description: An entry per each PTP server to which this slave clock is allowed to synchronize. All Announce and other PTP messages sent by master clock which is not in the shePtpAcceptableMasterTable will be ignored, e.g. not considered by Best Master Clock algorithm.

shePtpAcceptableMasterIndex.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterIndex
shePtpAcceptableMasterIndex.description: Index for table, Count of configured acceptable master entries.

shePtpAcceptableMasterNetworkProtocol.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterNetworkProtocol
shePtpAcceptableMasterNetworkProtocol.description: Supported PTP transport protocol is only IP/UDP.

shePtpAcceptableMasterProtocolAddressLen.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterProtocolAddressLength
shePtpAcceptableMasterProtocolAddressLen.description: Supported PTP transport protocol is only IP/UDP so address length is always 4.

shePtpAcceptableMasterProtocolAddress.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterProtocolAddress
shePtpAcceptableMasterProtocolAddress.description: The IP address of the configured acceptable master.

shePtpAcceptableMasterPriority.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterPriority
shePtpAcceptableMasterPriority.description: This attribute is an alternate priority to be used to determine best master clock. If shePtpAcceptableMasterPriority is 0 it shall have no effect on computation determination of best master clock. If the value of shePtpAcceptableMasterPriority is greater than 0, the value of priority1 in the Announce message from the remote port shall be replaced by the value of the shePtpAcceptableMasterPriority for purposes of determining best master clock.

shePtpAcceptableMasterUnicast.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterUnicast
shePtpAcceptableMasterUnicast.description: This attribute determines the communications type used for PTP messages (unicast/multicast). It depends on destination IP address type of the packets (master clock port address or IP multicast domain). It is set to TRUE if unicast communication is used or set to FALSE if multicast addresses are used (standard PTP assigned IP multicast addresses).

shePtpAcceptableMasterMinTimingPktSize.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterMinTimingPktSize
shePtpAcceptableMasterMinTimingPktSize.description: The minimum packet size to use for packets carrying timing information. This is the total packet size after all protocol headers have been added, but excluding the Ethernet FCS. The required packet size is achieved by adding padding bytes to the minimum timing packet size required by the PTP protocol. If the specified value is less than the minimum quired by the protocol it will be ignored. Hence specifying zero will always use the standard packet size - no padding will be added to the PTP messages.

shePtpAcceptableMasterSyncStatus.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterSyncStatus
shePtpAcceptableMasterSyncStatus.description: This parameter show the clock recovery algorithm status which is an enum of values { FREERUN, HOLDOVER, ACQUIRING, ACQUIRED }. For normal operation, i.e. when this slave clock is synchronized to any master clock that attribute will have 'ACQUIRED' value.

shePtpAcceptableMasterControlRequest.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterControlRequest
shePtpAcceptableMasterControlRequest.description: createPtpAcceptableMasterTableEntry (12): shePtpAcceptableMasterControlProtocolAddress shePtpAcceptableMasterControlPriority shePtpAcceptableMasterControlUnicast shePtpAcceptableMasterControlMinTimingPktSize modifyPtpAcceptableMasterTableEntry (13): shePtpAcceptableMasterControlIndex shePtpAcceptableMasterControlProtocolAddress shePtpAcceptableMasterControlPriority shePtpAcceptableMasterControlUnicast shePtpAcceptableMasterControlMinTimingPktSize deletePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntry (14): shePtpAcceptableMasterControlIndex

shePtpAcceptableMasterControlStatus.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterControlStatus
shePtpAcceptableMasterControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

shePtpAcceptableMasterControlTimer.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterControlTimer
shePtpAcceptableMasterControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shePtpAcceptableMasterControlReqResult.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterControlReqResult
shePtpAcceptableMasterControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

shePtpAcceptableMasterControlTimeStamp.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterControlTimeStamp
shePtpAcceptableMasterControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shePtpAcceptableMasterControlIndex.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterControlIndex
shePtpAcceptableMasterControlIndex.description: The index of acceptable master table entry for configuration.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTable.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTable
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTable.description: The table is used by this slave clock to start negotiation of message rates with required master clocks. It is only meaningful when unicast communications is used and shePtpPortDSUnicastNegotiationEnabled attribute of corresponding clock port is set to TRUE.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterEntry.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterEntry
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterEntry.description: Request, that the master identified by this antry, transmits unicast Announce, Sync and Delay_Resp messages to that slave clock will be sent. PTP message rates autonegotiation will be performed with a master identified by this entry.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterNetworkProto.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterNetworkProtocol
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterNetworkProto.description: Supported PTP transport protocol is only IP/UDP.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterProtocolAddr.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterProtocolAddressLength
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterProtocolAddr.description: Supported PTP transport protocol is only IP/UDP so address length is always 4.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterProtocolAddr.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterProtocolAddress
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterProtocolAddr.description: Protocol address of master clock port to which this slave clock is to be sending unicast message GRANT REQUESTS, i.e. unicast discovery of the master which port address is added to the shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTable shall be in effect right after an entry is added (if this address is not yet in the shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTable and PTP message rates are not already negotiated). Please NOTE that the master's port address must be added in advance to the shePtpAcceptableMasterTable too.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlContr.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlControlStatus
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlContr.description: The status of a user command.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlTimer.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlTimer
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlReqRe.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlReqResult
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlReqRe.description: The result of the last user command.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlTimeS.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlTimeStamp
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlTimeS.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlPortD.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlPortDsNumber
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlPortD.description: The index 1 of unicast discovery master table entry for configuration - portDs index.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlIndex.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlIndex
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterControlIndex.description: The index 2 of unicast discovery master table.

shePtpAdminStateChanged.name: shePtpAdminStateChanged
shePtpAdminStateChanged.description: The administrative state of the PTP subsystem has changed.

shePtpDefaultDataSetModified.name: shePtpDefaultDataSetModified
shePtpDefaultDataSetModified.description: Notification for successful PTP default data set configuration.

shePtpPortConfigDataModified.name: shePtpPortConfigDataModified
shePtpPortConfigDataModified.description: Notification for successfull PTP port config data configuration.

shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryCreated.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryCreated
shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryCreated.description: Notification for successfull create of PTP acceptable master table entry.

shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryModified.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryModified
shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryModified.description: Notification for successfull modify of PTP acceptable master table entry.

shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryDeleted.name: shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryDeleted
shePtpAcceptableMasterTableEntryDeleted.description: Notification for successfull delete of PTP acceptable master table entry.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryCr.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryCreated
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryCr.description: Notification for successfull create of PTP unicast discovery master table entry.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryMo.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryModified
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryMo.description: Notification for successfull modify of PTP unicast discovery master table entry.

shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryDe.name: shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryDeleted
shePtpUnicastDiscoveryMasterTableEntryDe.description: Notification for successfull delete of PTP unicast discovery master table entry.

shePtpForeignMasterTableChanged.name: shePtpForeignMasterTableChanged
shePtpForeignMasterTableChanged.description: This trap will be send if the foreign master table changes because of new detected masters or a alraedy detected entry is lost.

shePtpSynchronizationAlarm.name: shePtpSynchronizationAlarm
shePtpSynchronizationAlarm.description: This alarm will be activated if the ptp sync module is enabled and no external sync master was found or connection could not be established or was lost.

shePtpIpHostInterfaceAlarm.name: shePtpIpHostInterfaceAlarm
shePtpIpHostInterfaceAlarm.description: This alarm will be activated: 1. If the ptp sync module is enabled and no valid IpHostInterface configuration could be detected. -> Configure a valid host interface via sheSystemIpHostTable. 2. The used interface was reconfigured during ongoing PTP session. -> The PTP module must be restarted.

shePtpCompliance.name: shePtpCompliance
shePtpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement the PTP MIB.
